In the Matter of ALTON BARIUM PRODUCTS COMPANY, a Corporation, Bankrupt. Anna HOEHN and D. Wolff & Sons, Inc., v. MONSANTO CHEMICAL WORKS, a Corporation. No. 4897. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Jan. 26, 1933. Jack McDonald, of Alton, Ill., for appellant. M. D. Powell, of Edwardsville, Ill., and B. J. O’Neill, of Alton, Ill., for appellee.

Before ALSCHULER, EVANS, and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

In the matter of the motion of appellees to dismiss the appeal, it is ordered that the said motion of appellees in the above-entitled cause to dismiss the appeal be, and it is hereby, granted, for the reason that the order appealed from is not an appealable order.
